author: Rick Cantu
title: Cedar Creek flying high after previous seasons of futility
text:
A new strain of Cedar fever has hit Central Texas, and it has nothing to do with itchy eyes and sensitive noses.
Cedar Park remains the top-ranked Class 5A football team in Texas with a 6-0 record. Cedar Ridge, the Round Rock school in just its fourth year of varsity football, is 6-0, too.
